Wash and dry produce.

Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Trim and finely dice @mini cucumber{1}. Finely dice @tomato{1}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}. Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

== Bulgur ==

In a #small pot{}, combine @bulgur wheat{1/2%cup}, 1 cup water, @harissa powder{1/2%tsp} (you'll use more later), and @salt{1/2%tsp}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until water has absorbed and bulgur is tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in step 5.

== Feta Sauce ==

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, @feta cheese{2%tbsp} (you'll use the remaining feta later), and a large drizzle of @olive oil{}. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Salmon ==

Pat @salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with @harissa powder{1/2%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (Use more harissa powder if you like things spicy.)

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add salmon and cook (skin sides down) until skin is crisp, ~{5-7%minutes}, then flip and cook until cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Transfer to a #plate{}.

> Salmon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

== Tabbouleh ==

Meanwhile, squeeze juice from half a lemon into a #large bowl{}. Whisk in lemon zest, @olive oil{2%tbsp}, and @salt{1/4%tsp}.

If necessary, drain any excess water from cooked bulgur; stir bulgur into bowl with dressing along with cucumber, tomato, scallions, half the cilantro, and @feta cheese{1/2%cup}(crumbled). Taste and season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Thinly slice salmon crosswise.

Divide tabbouleh between #bowls{} or #plates{}. Top with salmon. Drizzle with feta sauce and sprinkle with remaining cilantro. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> This recipe is a one-bowl feast that's positively bursting with Middle Eastern–inspired flavors, featuring lemony bulgur topped with harissa-spiced salmon and a drizzle of creamy feta sauce.